<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                        Department</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington, D.
                                        C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-03"><hi rend="italic">November 3,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Nashville</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Colon:</hi></p>
                        <p>In the interest of peace make every effort to prevent Government troops
                            at Colon from proceeding to Panama. The transit of the Isthmus must be
                            kept open and order maintained. Acknowledge.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Darling</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>